<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Smith Agrees to Terms With T'Wolves </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MINNEAPOLIS (AP) -- Free agent forward Joe Smith has agreed to  
terms with the Minnesota Timberwolves 
</P>
<P>
	Smith said today he signed a one-year, $2.2 million deal because  
he liked playing alongside Kevin Garnett and liked the direction 
the team was headed. 
</P>
<P>
	``I definitely could have gotten a better deal elsewhere but  
this wasn't about my financial state,'' Smith said. ``When I came 
here last year I wanted to put the fun back in the game and be on a 
team that plays hard every night. I found that here. I like playing 
with Kevin and I like playing for Flip Saunders'' 
</P>
<P>
	Saunders, coach and general manager, said: ``Joe and KG (Kevin  
Garnett) really complement each other and give us two of the best 
shot-blocking forwards in the game today.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Smith appeared in 43 games for the Timberwolves last season,  
averaging 13.7 points, 8.3 rebounds and 1.5 blocks. He was ninth in 
the league in offensive rebounding with 3.6 per game. 
</P>
<P>
	Smith was the No. 1 overall selection in the 1995 draft when he  
was chosen by the Golden State Warriors. He was traded to the 
Philadelphia 76ers on Feb. 17, 1998, and signed with the Wolves as 
a free agent last season. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
