<HEADLINE> M's Rodriguez Has Suspension Upheld </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TORONTO (AP) -- Frankie Rodriguez's seven-game suspension was  
upheld Tuesday by AL president Gene Budig, who cut Jay Buhner's 
suspension from four games to three. 
</P>
<P>
	Rodriguez immediately began serving his penalty, which stemmed  
from an Aug. 6 brawl with the New York Yankees. Budig heard the 
appeals Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	``I would have thought my suspension would have been reduced by  
at least one day,'' said Rodriguez, who charged after and punched 
Yankees catcher Joe Girardi. ``How many times does a reliever get 
more than five games?'' 
</P>
<P>
	Buhner, suspended for a fight with Los Angeles Dodgers on July  
11, will start his suspension after Rodriguez's is completed. 
  	   	
</P>
