<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Cardinals Send Jimenez to Minors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. LOUIS (AP) -- Rookie Jose Jimenez, whose no-hitter against  
the Arizona Diamondbacks was a bright spot in an otherwise 
inconsistent season, was optioned to Triple-A Memphis Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	The Cardinals recalled Rick Heiserman, 26, a right-hander who  
was the closer at Memphis. Heiserman pitched 1 2-3 scoreless 
innings in Tuesday's 6-5 win over the Philadelphia Phillies. 
</P>
<P>
	Jimenez, a right-hander, beat Randy Johnson and the Diamondbacks  
1-0 with his no-hitter on June 25 at Phoenix. A little over a week 
later, Jimenez and the Cardinals again shut out Johnson and the 
Diamondbacks at home. 
</P>
<P>
	But otherwise, Jimenez has struggled. After going 3-0 in a  
September callup last season, Jimenez is 5-12 with a 5.81 ERA in 
1999. In his last start Sunday, Jimenez lasted just two innings 
against the Chicago Cubs, giving up five earned runs and five hits 
-- including two Sammy Sosa homers. 
</P>
<P>
	Jimenez said he has some mechanical flaws to work out.  
</P>
<P>
	``I'm a little surprised, but I'll find my way back,'' he said.  
</P>
<P>
	Manager Tony La Russa said Jimenez likely will be recalled Sept.  
1, when active rosters expand from 25 to 40. 
</P>
<P>
	``His results have been mixed,'' La Russa said. ``I think he's  
learning from his ups and downs.'' 
</P>
<P>
	La Russa wasn't sure who would replace Jimenez in the rotation,  
but said he was leaning toward Juan Acevedo, 5-4 with a 6.05 ERA. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
