<DOCNO> APW19990817.0042 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-17 20:20:12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Lycos Reports Improved Earnings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WALTHAM, Mass. (AP) -- Lycos Inc., a leading search and directory  
site on the World Wide Web, reported a 137 percent surge in 
fourth-quarter revenue, helping the company post operating earnings 
that beat analysts' expectations. 
</P>
<P>
	For the quarter ended July 31,Lycos reported a net loss of $21.4  
million, or 24 cents a share, compared with a net loss of $6.8 
million, or 9 cents a share, for the same period a year ago. 
</P>
<P>
	Excluding costs related to mergers aquisitions and other  
one-time expenses, the company earned $605,000, or 1 cent per 
share, up from a $703,000, or 1 cent per share, loss in the same 
period last year. 
</P>
<P>
	That beat analysts' expectations that the company would break  
even for the quarter. 
</P>
<P>
	Revenues grew to $45.1 million, a 137 percent increase over the  
$19 million Lycos took in last year in the same period. 
</P>
<P>
	But Lycos has been spending freely, incurring a number of  
significant costs in recent months, including $265 million to 
acquire three companies: WhoWhere?, Wired Digital and Internet 
Music Distribution Inc. 
</P>
<P>
	Lycos also ended its fiscal year July 31, posting a  
5-cent-a-share, $6.2 million loss on the year, adjusting for the 
one-time expenses, compared to a 6-cent-a-share, $3.6 million loss 
in the year ending July 31, 1998. 
</P>
<P>
	Including one-time expenses, Lycos lost $52 million, or 60 cents  
a share, in fiscal 1999, up from $28.4 million, or 46 cents a 
share, the year before. 
</P>
<P>
	But revenues skyrocketed from fiscal 1998 to fiscal 1999,  
increasing 142 percent, from $56.1 million to $135.5 million. 
</P>
<P>
	Waltham, Mass.-based Lycos is a leading Internet portal, a sort  
of jumping off point for people surfing the World Wide Web. 
</P>
<P>
	The earnings statement was released after the close of trading  
Tuesday on the Nasdaq Stock Market. Lycos' stock closed the session 
up $1.87 1/2 at $42.31 1/4. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
