<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Fla. Crossing Guard Hit by Pickup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LAKELAND, Fla. (AP) -- A school crossing guard was hit by a  
pickup truck after pushing two youngsters to safety. 
</P>
<P>
	Jill Cook, 66, was hospitalized in satisfactory condition with a  
broken knee, hip and ribs. 
</P>
<P>
	Mrs. Cook pushed 7-year-old Amber Stringer and 10-year-old Tony  
Stringer out of the way of the pickup Monday near Crystal Lake 
Elementary. 
</P>
<P>
	``How can you possibly thank someone for saving your kids'  
lives?'' said Christina Stringer, the children's mother. ``Even 
when Jill was on the ground, all she asked about was if my kids 
were safe. She is one incredible woman.'' 
</P>
<P>
	At the school Tuesday, many of the 600 youngsters worked on  
cards and posters for Mrs. Cook. 
</P>
<P>
	Mrs. Cook ``said she was just protecting the lives of children  
like she was trained to do,'' said a daughter, Joyce Cook. 
</P>
<P>
	No immediate charges were filed against the driver.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
