<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Suns Re-Sign Randy Livingston </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PHOENIX (AP) -- The Phoenix Suns on Tuesday re-signed point guard  
Randy Livingston to a multiyear contract. 
</P>
<P>
	Livingston, a backup to starter Jason Kidd, was signed by the  
Suns on May 4, prior to the team's regular-season finale against 
Minnesota. 
</P>
<P>
	Livingston scored 12 points in 22 minutes against the  
Timberwolves and then was put on the playoff roster, averaging 5.3 
points and 2.3 rebounds in 8 minutes over three games against 
Portland. 
</P>
<P>
	Before signing with the Suns last season, Livingston played for  
Sioux Falls of the CBA. He previously played in the NBA for Houston 
(1996-97) and Atlanta (1997-98). 
</P>
<P>
	Citing team policy, Suns spokesman Scott Leightman said length  
of the contract and salary terms were not being disclosed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
