<DOCNO> APW19990817.0070 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-17 17:50:11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> washington </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Boeing To Cooperate With Govt Probe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- The Boeing Co. agreed Tuesday to give the  
Labor Department access to facilities and records the government 
wants in its enforcement of affirmative action and 
nondiscrimination requirements on federal contractors. 
</P>
<P>
	The Labor Department sought the documents and information in an  
investigation of a Boeing employee's class-action complaint 
alleging race discrimination at the company's commercial aircraft 
facility in Seattle. 
</P>
<P>
	The employee is among black Boeing workers who filed a lawsuit  
contending they were treated with hostility and were passed over 
for promotions that went to less-qualified white workers. 
</P>
<P>
	Boeing also agreed to cooperate with a routine compliance review  
at a training facility in Mesa, Ariz. 
</P>
<P>
	A hearing is scheduled next month on a government allegation  
that Boeing has also thwarted Labor Department compliance reviews 
at commercial aircraft and military space and defense facilities in 
Wichita, Kan. 
</P>
<P>
	``In the interests of preserving our ongoing relationship with  
the agency, we agreed to settle on two of the issues and are still 
negotiating in the third case and hope to have it resolved 
shortly,'' Boeing spokesman Larry McCracken said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	The Labor Department filed the three complaints against Boeing  
in July with administrative law judges, who offer a first avenue 
adjudicating disputes outside the normal court system. 
</P>
<P>
	Judge Stuart Levin, a Labor Department administration judge  
here, will retain jurisdiction over the settlement for up to one 
year while the government investigations are completed. 
</P>
<P>
	With $11 billion in government business last year and 230,000  
workers nationwide, Seattle-based Boeing is the second-largest 
defense contractor after Lockheed Martin Corp. 



  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
