<DOCNO> APW19990817.0079 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-17 13:30:12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE>  Matthaeus Signs With MetroStars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- German star Lothar Matthaeus signed a one-year  
contract Tuesday to play in the Major League Soccer and will report 
to the New York-New Jersey MetroStars early next year. 
</P>
<P>
	Matthaeus, 38, will reportedly earn approximately $1 million in  
the deal, a combination of his $250,000 salary plus bonus and 
incentives from sponsorship and endorsement deals. 
</P>
<P>
	Matthaeus, who has played in the most World Cup games (25) and  
is third on the career list with 139 caps, first announced his 
intention to move to the United States and the MLS in June 
following weeks of speculation. 
</P>
<P>
	However, the MLS refused to say anything more than that it had  
discussions with Matthaeus until it received written assurance from 
Matthaeus' German club, Bayern Munich. 
</P>
<P>
	``This is a very positive development for the league to be able  
to secure the services of such a high-profile player like Lothar 
Matthaeus,'' MLS executive vice president Ivan Gazidis said. 
``Given the budget and the world we live in, it was not the easiest 
job. ... It will raise the awareness of MLS outside the boundaries 
of the U.S.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Matthaeus will be released from Bayern on Jan. 1. The first half  
of the Bundesliga season ends Dec. 18, with the German season 
taking a six-week break before it resumes play Feb. 5. The MLS 
season begins in March. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
