<DOCNO> APW19990817.0095 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-17 19:30:13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Marlins Assign Orie To minors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Florida Marlins infielder Kevin Orie, on the  
disabled list since July 1, was sent Triple-A Calgary on an injury 
rehabilitation assignment today. 
</P>
<P>
	Orie, 26, sprained his left wrist on Aug. 3 while he was with  
Calgary on a previous rehab assignment. Orie, hitting .266 with 
five homers and 25 RBIs, was sidelined by partial tear of his left 
quadriceps before he hurt his wrist. 
</P>
<P>
	Orie's career has been plagued by injuries since he was selected  
by the Chicago Cubs in the 1993 amateur draft. 
</P>
<P>
	He spent four months on the disabled list in 1994 with a  
cartilage tear of his right wrist. He was on the DL for three weeks 
in 1996 with a separated right shoulder, and in 1997 Orie was on 
the DL for a month with right shoulder inflammation. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
