<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-17 11:31:01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE>  Matthaeus Signs With MetroStars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Lothar Matthaeus, one of the Germany's  
best-known players, signed a one-year contract to play in the Major 
League Soccer and will report to the New York-New Jersey MetroStars 
early next year, an MLS source said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	The contract was to be announced later Tuesday on the league's  
weekly telephone news conference with reporters. 
</P>
<P>
	The 38-year-old Matthaeus will earn approximately $1 million in  
the deal, a combination of his $250,000 salary plus bonus and 
incentives from sponsorship and endorsement deals. 
</P>
<P>
	Matthaeus, who has played in the most World Cup games (25) and  
is third all-time with 139 caps, first announced his intention to 
move to the United States and MLS in June. That followed weeks of 
speculation. However, MLS refused to say anything more than it had 
discussions with Matthaeus until it had received written assurance 
from Matthaeus' German club Bayern Munich. 
</P>
<P>
	The MLS source said the league had received documents  
guaranteeing MLS that Bayern will release Matthaeus after the 
club's final game of the first half of the Bundesliga season on 
Dec. 18 against Werder Bremen. The German season takes a six-week 
break and then resumes on Feb. 5. 
</P>
<P>
	The MLS season begins in March.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
