<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-17 14:53:58 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE>  Fortner To Coach Indianapolis WNBA </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	INDIANAPOLIS (AP) -- Nell Fortner, coach of the U.S. women's  
basketball team, was hired Tuesday to coach the new Indianapolis 
WNBA franchise, starting in its second season. 
</P>
<P>
	The former Purdue coach will miss the team's first season next  
summer because of the Sydney Games. 
</P>
<P>
	``But I'll definitely have my eyeball on it and my hand on the  
telephone,'' she said at a news conference at Market Square Arena. 
</P>
<P>
	An interim coach will guide the still-unnamed team through its  
inaugural season. 
</P>
<P>
	The 40-year-old Fortner, an assistant coach for the U.S. women's  
team in 1995-96, came to Purdue in 1996-97 and led the Boilermakers 
to a 17-11 record and a share of the Big Ten championship. She was 
the conference coach of the year but left the Boilermakers after 
just one season to become the coach of the U.S. national team. 
</P>
<P>
	Since then, she has compiled a 54-12 record in international  
competition and won the 1998 world championship. 
</P>
<P>
	Fortner, a Jackson, Miss., native and 1982 graduate of the  
University of Texas, spent eight years as an assistant at Stephen 
F. Austin and Louisiana Tech. 
</P>
<P>
	``I love college ball,'' she said. ``But I think this is the  
perfect time for me to step into the WNBA, to go from coaching the 
national team, the pros at that level, and then to continue on with 
it. 
</P>
<P>
	``As young girls grow up and continue to grow and believe  
they're going to be in the WNBA, our product will get better. So I 
think this is where I belong.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Indianapolis joins Miami, Portland and Seattle as the new WNBA  
franchises, boosting the league to 16 teams. 
</P>
<P>
	Each new franchise is conditional, however -- it must sell at  
least 5,500 season tickets by Oct. 15. The Indianapolis team has 
sold about 3,000 season tickets so far. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW19990817.0102 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-17 14:53:58 </DATE_TIME>
