	``As young girls grow up and continue to grow and believe  
they're going to be in the WNBA, our product will get better. So I 
think this is where I belong.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Indianapolis joins Miami, Portland and Seattle as the new WNBA  
franchises, boosting the league to 16 teams. 
</P>
<P>
	Each new franchise is conditional, however -- it must sell at  
least 5,500 season tickets by Oct. 15. The Indianapolis team has 
sold about 3,000 season tickets so far. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
