<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Colts Sign Veteran RB Vaughn Hebron </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TERRE HAUTE, Ind. (AP) -- The Indianapolis Colts on Tuesday  
signed running back Vaughn Hebron, a member of Denver's Super Bowl 
championship teams the past two years. 
</P>
<P>
	The 5-foot-8, 192-pound Hebron was signed after a morning  
workout and was returning kicks during afternoon practice. 
</P>
<P>
	``Every team prides itself on bringing a player in that's been a  
part of a winning organization and hopefully it becomes a kind of 
fever,'' said Hebron, originally signed as a free agent in April 
1993 by Philadelphia and waived by the Eagles prior to the start of 
the 1996 season. Seven days later, the Broncos signed the former 
Virginia Tech star as a free agent. 
</P>
<P>
	In six seasons Hebron has played in 79 games with seven starts.  
He has averaged 24.1 yards on 158 kickoff returns and 4.2 yards per 
carry. He also has 41 receptions for 303 yards. 
</P>
<P>
	``I've been there. I know what it takes, so from that standpoint  
you know if a team is doing everything it needs to be done to get 
to that (championship) level. At the same time, I can recognize 
when it is not,'' said Hebron, who was cut by Denver after last 
season. 
</P>
<P>
	Hebron was the Broncos' backup to Terrell Davis, the NFL's MVP  
last season. He had only 58 carries for 253 yards the past two 
seasons. 
</P>
<P>
	``Kick returns, that's where I made my niche in,'' Hebron said.  
``Whatever you ask of me, I'm that man.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Coach Jim Mora said the Colts felt they needed another back  
because Darick Holmes is expected to be out for at least six weeks 
with a fracture near his right ankle. 
</P>
<P>
	``He's been in the league six years. He's been a real good  
kickoff return guy, and a running back,'' Mora said of Hebron. ``He 
can catch the ball out of the backfield, so we decided to sign 
him.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Mora said he might use the team's newest member to return kicks  
in Saturday's exhibition game at New Orleans. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
