<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Treasury Bill Interest Rate Rises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- The interest rate on 52-week Treasury bills  
rose in Tuesday's auction to the highest level in a year. 
</P>
<P>
	The discount rate was 4.945 percent, up from 4.710 percent at  
the last auction on July 20. It was the highest rate since 52-week 
bills sold for 5.000 percent on Aug. 18, 1998. 
</P>
<P>
	The bills will carry an equivalent coupon interest rate of 5.224  
percent with each $10,000 in face value selling for $9,500. 
</P>
<P>
	Sales totaled $10 billion out of bids of $25 billion.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
