<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Astros' Bell Placed on DL </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HOUSTON (AP) -- Houston Astros right fielder Derek Bell was  
placed on the team's 15-day disabled list Tuesday, a day after 
straining his left groin. 
</P>
<P>
	Bell was hitting .244 with 11 homers and 61 RBIs.  
</P>
<P>
	Astros manager Larry Dierker shuffled his starting outfield  
Tuesday night, moving center fielder Carl Everett to right field. 
Glen Barker started in center field and Lance Berkman went to left. 
</P>
<P>
	``We'll give Barker a couple of games and hit him in the two  
spot and see if we can get some energy at the spot,'' Dierker said. 
``We know he can play defense and run the bases. We need to find 
out if he can get on base.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Barker, the Astros' fastest runner, has played in 60 games and  
is hitting .333 with six RBIs and 13 steals. 
</P>
<P>
	Russ Johnson was recalled from Class Triple-A New Orleans to  
take Bell's roster spot. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
