<HEADLINE> New AP Chief of Bureau in Taiwan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Bill Foreman, a newsman on the International  
Desk of The Associated Press, has been named chief of bureau in 
Taiwan. 
</P>
<P>
	The appointment was announced Monday by AP President Louis D.  
Boccardi. 
</P>
<P>
	Foreman will report to Hong Kong Chief of Bureau Bob Liu.  
</P>
<P>
	Foreman began his AP career in 1995 as a newsman in Kansas City  
and transferred to the International Desk two years later. 
</P>
<P>
	He is a native of Baltimore and earned a bachelor's degree from  
the University of Kansas and a master's degree from the University 
of Maryland. 
</P>
<P>
	Before joining the AP, he worked as a reporter for the  
Springfield, Mo., News-Leader and the Columbia, Mo., Daily Tribune. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
