<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that moved substantially or traded  
heavily Tuesday on the New York Stock Exchange and Nasdaq Stock 
Market. 

</P>
<P>
                               *NYSE    	

</P>
<P>
 *Hewlett Packard, down 5 3/4 at 104 1/2    	
</P>
<P>
	The computer maker reported earnings of $853 million, or 81  
cents a share, in its fiscal third quarter, including the cost of 
separating into two companies. Without the costs, HP would have 
earned 85 cents per share, but some unpublished estimates had 
called for 87 cents per share. 

</P>
<P>
 *Burlington Resources, down 2 9/16 at 42 3/4    	
</P>
<P>
	Burlington has agreed to buy Canada's Poco Petroleums Ltd. for  
$1.75 billion in stock. The deal will make Burlington the 
fourth-largest natural gas producer in North America. 

</P>
<P>
 *Tiffany &AMP; Co., up 6 5/16 at 53    	
</P>
<P>
	The upscale jeweler earned 31 cents per share in the second  
quarter, up from 19 cents per share in the second quarter of 1998. 
Tiffany said same-store sales rose 12 percent and international 
sales rose 30 percent during the quarter. 

</P>
<P>
 *Diamond Home Services Inc., down 13/32 at 4 29/32    	
</P>
<P>
	Diamond said July sales fell about 30 percent, due to operating  
inefficiencies in the installed home-improvement segment. Diamond, 
a marketer and contractor of installed home-improvement products, 
said it also expects poor results in August. 

</P>
<P>
                              *NASDAQ   	

</P>
<P>
 *CE Software Holdings Inc., up 1 1/16 at 6 1/2    	
</P>
<P>
	CE Software, of West Des Moines, Iowa, is considering several  
strategic initiatives, including forming a technology unit, or 
selling or spinning off its CE Software Inc. operating company. 

</P>
<P>
 *Ligand Pharmaceuticals Inc., down 2 3/4 at 7 3/16    	
</P>
<P>
	Ligand, which had estimated that it would turn a profit in 1999,  
said it will not be profitable until 2000. Ligand, a drug 
development company, said its second-quarter results indicate that 
it will take longer than expected to achieve profitability. 

</P>
<P>
 *8x8 Inc., up 1 3/4 at 4 7/8    	
</P>
<P>
	The company signed an agreement with a unit of Lucent  
Technologies to jointly market an Internet telephony system that 
includes call waiting, call forwarding and three-way calling. The 
system is intended for service providers and enterprise customers. 

</P>
<P>
 *Audible Inc., up 2 5/8 at 16 1/2    	
</P>
<P>
	Shares rose for a second straight session after Audible expanded  
its relationship with Microsoft Corp. and RealNetworks Inc. 
Audible's spoken audio content will become available in Microsoft's 
Windows Media Player and RealNetworks' RealPlayer. 

</P>
<P>
 *Recoton Corp., down 19/32 at 7 15/16    	
</P>
<P>
	Recoton lost 67 cents per share in the second quarter, compared  
to a profit of 26 cents per share in last year's second quarter. 
The company, a maker of consumer electronic products, said it will 
cut jobs and consolidate certain business units. 



  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
