<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Moderate Quake Hits Northern Calif. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BOLINAS, Calif. (AP) -- A moderate earthquake rocked this  
Northern California town Tuesday evening, swaying office buildings 
in San Francisco and rattling homes 50 miles south in San Jose. 
</P>
<P>
	The quake with a preliminary magnitude of 5.0 happened at 6:06  
p.m. near the San Andreas Fault, 30 miles northwest of San 
Francisco, said U.S. Geological Survey spokesman Dale Cox. 
</P>
<P>
	No injuries or damage were immediately reported.  
</P>
<P>
	The quake rocked cars and made streetlights swing in San  
Francisco. Items fell off shelves, and workers at San Jose 
International Airport felt the control tower shake. 
</P>
<P>
	``Usually it is more of a rolling. This was like an explosion,''  
said Toby Bisson, a utility operator at the Stinson Beach Water 
District just south of Bolinas. 
</P>
<P>
	He said the ground in his backyard rumbled for 10 or 15 seconds,  
frightening his 5-year-old daughter. 
</P>
<P>
	``She freaked out. She started crying. She said, 'I don't like  
earthquakes' and started running in the house. It took a while for 
her to come down. It was just loud and scary,'' Bisson said. 
</P>
<P>
	Skip Schwartz, executive director of the Audubon Canyon Ranch, a  
1,000-acre wildlife sanctuary in Bolinas, said none of the ranch's 
buildings were damaged and nobody was injured. 
</P>
<P>
	``It was so loud we thought a plane crashed nearby,'' Schwartz  
said. The sanctuary is on the edge of the San Andreas fault, and 
the quake sent the birds aloft. 
</P>
<P>
	``The birds got out of the trees and they were all up in the  
air. The noise and vibrations must have been profound for them, at 
the top of these hundred-foot tall redwoods,'' he said. 
</P>
<P>
	The USGS recorded four aftershocks over the next 2 1/2 hours within  
a mile of Bolinas. The first, a light 2.1-magnitude earthquake, 
happened at 6:41 p.m., followed by a 1.7-magnitude quake, one of 
2.0-magnitude and another of 2.2-magnitude. 
</P>
<P>
	Neither the San Francisco Police Department nor the San  
Francisco Department of Public Works reported any damage. 
</P>
<P>
	Business was running as usual at airports in Oakland and San  
Jose. Officials at San Francisco International Airport did not 
immediately return a telephone call. 
</P>
<P>
	No accidents were reported on any of the San Francisco Bay  
area's seven bridges. 
</P>
<P>
	Bolinas is about 17 miles northwest of San Francisco.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
