<HEADLINE> Ike Austin Arrives To Join Wizards </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Center Isaac Austin, obtained by the Wizards  
six days ago from Orlando, arrived in Washington on Tuesday a 
little lighter. 
</P>
<P>
	The 6-foot-10 Austin said he has lost 15 pounds since July 1 and  
is close to his ideal playing weight of 270 less than two months 
before training camp begins Oct. 5. 
</P>
<P>
	Austin lost 80 pounds prior to the 1996-97 season, then had a  
season with the Miami Heat that saw him named the NBA's most 
improved player. 
</P>
<P>
	While he doesn't have to lose as much weight this summer, he is  
eyeing another turnaround with the Wizards, his sixth NBA team. 
</P>
<P>
	``It kind of reminds me of being back in Miami,'' said Austin,  
who turns 30 Wednesday. ``We had a veteran team. This team kind of 
reminds me about that.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Austin averaged 9.7 points and 4.8 rebounds an outing in 49  
games last season for Orlando. The year before he averaged 12.7 
points per game in 52 contests with Miami and 15.2 points per 
outing in 26 games with the Clippers. He also has played in the NBA 
for Utah and Philadelphia. 
</P>
<P>
	``I want this to be the last stop,'' Austin said. ``This team  
has a lot of history. This is a great opportunity for me.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Washington traded Ben Wallace, Terry Davis, Tim Legler and Jeff  
McInnis to Orlando to get Austin. 
</P>
<P>
	The Wizards also announced the signing Tuesday of power forward  
Aaron Williams, who spent the past two seasons as a reserve in 
Seattle. Like Austin, the former Xavier standout will be playing 
for his sixth NBA team with Washington. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
