<HEADLINE> Arbitrator Gives York $1.4 Million </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TORONTO (AP) -- Ottawa Senators defenseman Jason York was awarded  
a one-year, $1.4-million contract by an arbitrator today. 
</P>
<P>
	York, represented by agent Don Meehan at Friday's arbitration  
hearing, was reportedly seeking $2 million a season. 
</P>
<P>
	The Senators, who notified other teams Monday that York was  
available to be traded, still can avoid following the arbitrator's 
decision by making the player an unrestricted free agent. 
</P>
<P>
	York, who had four goals and 31 assists in 79 games last season,  
was stunned to hear the Senators were trying to trade him. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm very disappointed,'' he told the Ottawa Citizen.  
  	   	
