<HEADLINE> Outlaws Gang Members Arrested in NC </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHARLOTTE, N.C. (AP) -- Eleven members of the Outlaws Motorcycle  
Club of North Carolina were arrested Tuesday on racketeering, 
firearms and drug conspiracy charges. 
</P>
<P>
	``We are continuing to place special emphasis on the targeting  
of allegedly violent drug organizations,'' U.S. Attorney Mark 
Calloway said after the arrests were made. 
</P>
<P>
	An indictment was returned on Aug. 4 by a federal grand jury; it  
remained sealed until the arrests were made Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	The indictment charged individuals, described by authorities as  
current or former members of the motorcycle gang, with conspiracy 
to distribute methamphetamine, LSD, cocaine, marijuana and Valium. 
Gang members were accused of possessing and distributing the drugs 
in Mecklenburg County since 1980. 
</P>
<P>
	If convicted, the 11 defendants face maximum penalties up to  
life in prison, a $4 million fine or both. 
</P>
<P>
	The charges were part of an ongoing federal probe named  
``Operation Speedball'' in which 33 people, including those 
arrested Tuesday, have been charged. 
  	   	
</P>
