<HEADLINE> Dow Gains 49; Nasdaq Is Up 31 / Wall Street Report  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- The Dow Jones industrial average is up 49 points  
in today's early going. Advancers on the New York Stock Exchange 
hold a 2-1 lead over decliners. 
</P>
<P>
	The Nasdaq Composite Index is up 31 points and the S&AMP;P 500 Index  
is up nine points. 
</P>
<P>
	Wall Street doesn't like surprises, and fortunately, it didn't  
get any this morning. 
</P>
<P>
	The Labor Department's July report on retail inflation came out  
as expected, with an increase of 0.3 percent. 
</P>
<P>
	The news sparked a rally in the bond market, and stocks have  
since joined in on the party as well. 
</P>
<P>
	Even with the benign report, many analysts still expect the  
Federal Reserve to boost short-term interest rates next week. 
</P>
<P>
	But any sort of drastic action from the Fed, such as a series of  
rate hikes, now seems much less likely. 
  	   	
</P>
